"{\"uid\": \"semafor.com-article-07-29-2024-olympics-china-glimpse-lgbtq-representation\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Intelligence for the New World Economy  Insights from Al Jazeera, Bloomberg, Time Magazine, The Washington Post, Nikkei Asia, and Reuters  Sign up for Semafor Flagship:The daily global news briefing you can trust.Read it now.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9353897360378383, \"rank\": 0.06907180310699672, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}, {\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"score\": 0.5769392598920275, \"rank\": 0.5859070419078899, \"text\": \"Bloomberg\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\"}, {\"begin\": 92, \"end\": 111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.58601091182678e-18, \"text\": \"The Washington Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\"}, {\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semafor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Semafor\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q24354\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semafor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semafor\"}, {\"begin\": 159, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flagship\", \"score\": 0.9630459937498042, \"rank\": 0.03837194428428734, \"text\": \"Flagship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flagship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flagship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a Chinese audience, the Paris Olympics opening ceremony Friday offered a rare glimpse of LGBTQ representation \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and a chance to air grievances against state media censorship.\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9056731559251735, \"rank\": 0.09241827086490584, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Broadcasters for CCTV appeared too stunned to speak during a drag performance and another involving men kissing.\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.7461001087329e-12, \"text\": \"CCTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, the topics \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cCCTV is silent\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cdrag queens\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d trended on Chinese social media platform Weibo for a full day alongsidevideo clipsof the live broadcast from Paris.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 598, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9056731559251735, \"rank\": 0.09241827086490584, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994012227463, \"rank\": 5.987776979846194e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some users lamented missing the broadcast, which aired during the night in China, while others praised the Olympics for the display of diversity.\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9863533965212785, \"rank\": 0.01285547715364084, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was a beautiful night to stay up for,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d wrote one Weibo user.\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999970441, \"rank\": 1.5460315289369864e-12, \"text\": \"Weibo\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After fumbling the broadcast, Chinese social media users mocked CCTV as becoming \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWesternized\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d as a play on the government\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s stance that LGBTQ rights are aWestern ideathat threaten Chinese values.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 952, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9056731559251735, \"rank\": 0.09241827086490584, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.7461001087329e-12, \"text\": \"CCTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\"}, {\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9056731559251735, \"rank\": 0.09241827086490584, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The phrase, however, has been used by Chinese people online to evade censorship and deride the authorities\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 draconian stance.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"score\": 0.9934365463898661, \"rank\": 0.005486898544564248, \"text\": \"Chinese people\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government has curbed college-run LGBTQ clubs, shut down social media accounts, and waged an online war against \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ceffeminate men,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and essentially excluded LGBTQ people from public life.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDespite morerestrictions on LGBT+ advocacy in China, the community has shown resilience,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Yuhsuan Chien, a China Dissent Monitor analyst, told Nikkei Aasia earlier this year, noting that government pressure has made online advocacy more common.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.999919986237806, \"rank\": 7.627380163626352e-05, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}, {\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9863533965212785, \"rank\": 0.01285547715364084, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9863533965212785, \"rank\": 0.01285547715364084, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1595, \"end\": 1601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_diaspora\", \"score\": 0.9679049721380245, \"rank\": 0.019604636115519592, \"text\": \"Nikkei\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_diaspora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_diaspora\"}, {\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aasia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999367901, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aasia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aasia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aasia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across the strait in Taiwan, same-sex marriage is permitted (China does not allow it), as are Pride parades, LGBTQ films, and drag performances.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.999994756517358, \"rank\": 4.799244710207339e-06, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9863533965212785, \"rank\": 0.01285547715364084, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gay_pride\", \"score\": 0.8420275600542626, \"rank\": 0.18760958362745223, \"text\": \"Pride\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gay_pride\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gay_pride\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this year, former president Tsai Ing-wen eveninvitedan award winning Taiwanese drag queen to perform at the Presidential Office Building.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tsai Ing-wen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\"}, {\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidential_Office_Building_(Republic_of_China)\", \"score\": 0.9999999993819984, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Presidential Office Building\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidential_Office_Building_(Republic_of_China)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidential_Office_Building_(Republic_of_China)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taiwan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s progress in LGBTQ rights in the generally conservative East Asia \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\\u00c2\\u00a0it was the first Asian territory to legalize same-sex marriage in 2019 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\\u00c2\\u00a0has helped it forge a distinct national identity, anddistinguish itselffrom China, The Washington Post wrote.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_people\", \"score\": 0.7790661852446068, \"rank\": 0.2821589551063611, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9863533965212785, \"rank\": 0.01285547715364084, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 2229, \"end\": 2248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.58601091182678e-18, \"text\": \"The Washington Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Support for the LGBTQ community has also become animportant aspectof young Taiwanese people\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sense of national identity, Nikkei Asia reported.\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2331, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwanese_people\", \"score\": 0.9853085030226622, \"rank\": 0.011602815994520971, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwanese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwanese_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for SemaforFlagship  Intelligence for the New World Economy\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": []}]}"